A016013.name: Probably an erroneous version of A016017.

A016014.name: Least k such that 2*n*k + 1 is a prime.

A016016.name: Number of iterations of Reverse and Add which lead to a palindrome, or -1 if no palindrome is ever reached.

A016017.name: Smallest k such that 1/k can be written as a sum of exactly 2 unit fractions in n ways.
formula: a(p) = 2^((p-1)/2) = 2^A005097(i) if p is the i-th prime. (End)
a(n) is the least k such that (tau(k^2) + 1)/2 = n. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Aug 01 2001

A016021.name: Number of permutations of {1,2,...,n} in which each element follows its proper divisors.

A016026.name: Smallest base relative to which n is palindromic.
formula: To put Fischer's comments in words: if n > 3 is a strictly non-palindromic number (A016038), then a(n) = n - 1. If n > 1 is a binary palindrome (A006995), then a(n) = 2. And if n > 1 is a decimal palindrome, then a(n) <= 10. - _Alonso del Arte_, Sep 15 2017

A016028.name: Expansion of (1 - x + x^4) / (1 - x)^3.
formula: Also, from the third term on, triangular numbers + 3. - _Alexandre Wajnberg_, Dec 10 2005
a(n) = binomial(n,2) - 3*n + 9, n>=3. a(n-3) = n^2/2 - 7*n/2 + 9, n>=4. - _Milan Janjic_, Dec 28 2007

A016031.name: De Bruijn's sequence: 2^(2^(n-1) - n): number of ways of arranging 2^n bits in circle so all 2^n consecutive strings of length n are distinct.
formula: Shifting once to the left gives the binomial transform of A323816. - _Gus Wiseman_, Feb 01 2019

A016032.name: Least positive integer that is the sum of two squares of positive integers in exactly n ways.

A016034.name: Numbers having n self generators (not necessarily primitive).

A016035.name: a(n) = Sum_{j|n, 1 < j < n} phi(j). Also a(n) = n - phi(n) - 1 for n > 1.
formula: For n > 1, a(n) = A051953(n) - 1. - _Antti Karttunen_, Mar 12 2018

A016036.name: Row sums of triangle A000369.
formula: a(n) = D^n(exp(x)) evaluated at x = 0, where D is the operator 1/(1-x)^3*d/dx. Cf. A001515, A015735 and A028575. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 25 2011

A016037.name: Map numbers to number of letters in English name; sequence gives number of steps to converge (to 4).

A016038.name: Strictly non-palindromic numbers: n is not palindromic in any base b with 2 <= b <= n-2.
formula: a(n) = A047811(n-4) for n > 4. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 08 2015

A016040.name: Integer part of Chebyshev's theta function: floor( log(Product_{k=1..n} prime(k)) ).
formula: a(n) ~ n log n by the prime number theorem. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Dec 11 2008

A016041.name: Primes that are palindromic in base 2 (but written here in base 10).

A016045.name: a(n) = smallest prime p(k) such that the gaps between the primes p(k), p(k+1), p(k+2), ..., p(k+n) are 2, 4, 6, ... 2n.
formula: a(n)=Min{x : x=prime; {x+2k}=primes following x for k=1, .., n}

A016046.name: First occurrence of exactly n identical terms in A007448.

A016047.name: Smallest prime factor of Mersenne numbers.

A016048.name: Least k such that (2*p_n)*k + 1 | Mersenne(p_n), p_n = n-th prime, n >= 2.

A016052.name: a(1) = 3; for n >= 1, a(n+1) = a(n) + sum of its digits.
formula: a(n) = A062028(a(n-1)) for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 14 2013
a(n) - a(n-1) = A084228(n+1). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jun 27 2014

A016054.name: Numbers n such that (13^n - 1)/12 is prime.

A016057.name: Pseudo-powers to base 3: n divides 2^n + 1, n not a power of 3.

A016061.name: a(n) = n*(n+1)*(4*n+5)/6.
formula: Partial sums of A014105. - _Jon Perry_, Jul 23 2003
a(n) = Sum_{i=0..n-1} 2*i^2 + i. - Jani Nurminen (slinky(AT)iki.fi), May 14 2006

A016062.name: Write down decimal expansion of Pi; divide up into chunks of minimal length so that chunks are increasing numbers and do not begin with 0.

A016064.name: Smallest side lengths of almost-equilateral Heronian triangles (sides are consecutive positive integers, area is a nonnegative integer).
formula: a(n) = 3 + floor((2 + sqrt(3))*a(n-1)), n >= 3. - _Rick L. Shepherd_, Sep 04 2005
E.g.f.: exp((2 + sqrt(3))*x) + exp((2 - sqrt(3))*x) - exp(x). - _Franck Maminirina Ramaharo_, Nov 12 2018
a(n) = a(-n) for all integer n. - _Michael Somos_, May 11 2019

A016067.name: Consider all ways of writing a number as p+2m^2 where p is 1 or a prime and m >= 0; sequence gives numbers that are expressible in at least 2 more ways than any smaller number.

A016069.name: Numbers n such that n^2 contains exactly 2 different digits.

A016070.name: Numbers n such that n^2 contains exactly 2 different digits, excluding 10^m, 2*10^m, 3*10^m.

A016072.name: Obsolete sequence of lower bounds for A028444.

A016075.name: Expansion of 1/((1-8*x)*(1-9*x)*(1-10*x)*(1-11*x)).
formula: If we define f(m,j,x)=sum(binomial(m,k)*stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k),k=j..m) then a(n-3)=f(n,3,8), (n>=3). - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009

A016078.name: Smallest number that is sum of 2 positive n-th powers in 2 different ways.
formula: If A230561(n) exists, then a(n) <= A230561(n) for n > 1, with equality at least for n = 2, and inequality at least for n = 3. - _Jonathan Sondow_, Oct 24 2013 [Comment edited by _N. J. A. Sloane_, Apr 03 2021]

A016082.name: Add 4, then reverse the decimal digits.

A016087.name: First nontrivial or multidigital Armstrong number to base n.

A016088.name: a(n) = smallest prime p such that Sum_{primes q = 2, ..., p} 1/q exceeds n.
formula: a(n) ~ Prime(Floor(e^e^n)) = A000040(A096232(n)) as n -> infinity (see comment in A223037). (end)

A016089.name: Numbers n such that n divides n-th Lucas number A000032(n).

A016090.name: a(n) = 16^(5^n) mod 10^n: Automorphic numbers ending in digit 6, with repetitions.

A016094.name: Expansion of 1/((1-9x)(1-10x)(1-11x)(1-12x)).
formula: If we define f(m,j,x) = Sum_{k=j..m} binomial(m,k)*Stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k) then a(n-3) = f(n,3,9), n >= 3. - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009

A016095.name: Triangular array T(n,k) read by rows, where T(n,k) = coefficient of x^n*y^k in 1/(1-x-y-(x+y)^2).
formula: G.f.: T(0)/2, where T(k) = 1 + 1/(1 - (2*k+1+ x*(1+y))*x*(1+y)/((2*k+2+ x*(1+y))*x*(1+y)+ 1/T(k+1) )); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Nov 06 2013

A016096.name: a(n+1) = a(n) + sum of its digits, with a(1) = 9.
formula: a(n) = A062028(a(n-1)) for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 14 2013

A016098.name: Number of crossing set partitions of {1,2,...,n}.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} S2(n,k) - binomial(2*n,n)/(n+1); S2(n,k) Stirling numbers of the second kind.

A016103.name: Expansion of 1/((1-4x)(1-5x)(1-6x)).
formula: If we define f(m,j,x) = Sum_{k=j..m} binomial(m,k)*Stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k) then a(n-2) = f(n,2,4), n >= 2. - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009
E.g.f.: (d^2/dx^2)(exp(4*x)*((exp(x)-1)^2)/2!). See the Sheffer triangle comment above. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 08 2011

A016104.name: 2^2^2^ ... 2^w (with n 2's), where w = 1.92878.....
formula: a(0) = 1, a(n) = the greatest prime less than 2^(a(n-1)+1). - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Oct 25 2006

A016105.name: Blum integers: numbers of the form p * q where p and q are distinct primes congruent to 3 (mod 4).

A016106.name: Nonpalindromic and "non-core" numbers that when squared give palindrome with odd number of digits.

A016107.name: Bachet's equation: X^2 + k = Y^3, k=999. The terms are values of X, corresponding Y are in A248481.

A016109.name: Expansion of 1/((1-7x)(1-8x)(1-9x)(1-10x)).
formula: If we define f(m,j,x) = Sum_{k=j..m} binomial(m,k)*Stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k) then a(n-3) = f(n,3,7), n >= 3. - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009

A016112.name: Smallest prime whose digit product is n, if possible; otherwise 0 if n is a prime > 7 or 1 if n has a prime factor > 7.

A016113.name: Numbers whose square is a palindrome with an even number of digits.

A016114.name: Circular primes (numbers that remain prime under cyclic shifts of digits).

A016115.name: Number of prime palindromes with n digits.

A016116.name: a(n) = 2^floor(n/2).
formula: The signed sequence (-1)^n*2^floor(n/2) has a(n) = (sqrt(2))^n(1/2 - sqrt(2)/4) + (-sqrt(2))^n(1/2 + sqrt(2)/4). It is the inverse binomial transform of A000129(n-1). - _Paul Barry_, Apr 21 2004
Diagonal sums of A046854. a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(floor(n/2), k). - _Paul Barry_, Jul 07 2004
a(n) = Sum_{k=0..floor(n/2)} binomial(floor(n/2), floor(k/2)). - _Paul Barry_, Jul 15 2004

A016119.name: Minimal number of cosets in an orthogonal sublattice of A_n (minimal number of paths in any trellis diagram).

A016120.name: Minimal number of cosets in an orthogonal sublattice of {A_n}* (minimal number of paths in any trellis diagram).

A016121.name: Number of sequences (a_1, a_2, ..., a_n) of length n with a_1 = 1 satisfying a_i <= a_{i+1} <= 2*a_i.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} A097712(n, k). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 24 2004
Equals the binomial transform of A008934 (number of tournament sequences): a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} C(n, k)*A008934(k). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Sep 18 2005

A016122.name: Decimal expansion of solution to log_10(x) = x - 4.

A016123.name: a(n) = (11^(n+1) - 1)/10.
formula: For analogs with primes 2, 3, 5, 7, 13 and 17 see: A000225, A003462, A003463, A023000, A091030 and A091045, respectively.

A016125.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)*(1-12*x)).
formula: a(n) = 12*a(n-1)+1 for n>0, a(0)=1. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 19 2010

A016127.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2*x)*(1-5*x)).
formula: Binomial transform of A020989. - _Paul Barry_, May 18 2003
For n > 2, a(n) = 9*a(n-1) - 24*a(n-2) + 20*a(n-3). - _Gary W. Adamson_, Dec 26 2007

A016129.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-6x)).
formula: a(n-1) = ((4+sqrt4)^n - (4-sqrt4)^n)/4 in Fibonacci form. - Al Hakanson (hawkuu(AT)gmail.com), Dec 31 2008
a(n) = det(|ps(i+2,j+1)|, 1 <= i,j <= n), where ps(n,k) are Legendre-Stirling numbers of the first kind (A129467). - _Mircea Merca_, Apr 06 2013

A016131.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-8x)).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{i=1...(2^n -1)} i*(i+1)/2. - _Ctibor O. Zizka_, Mar 03 2009

A016134.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-10x)).
formula: G.f.: 1/(1-12*x+20*x^2). - _Zerinvary Lajos_, Apr 27 2009 [corrected by _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 14 2011]
Convolution of A000079 and A011557. - _Michael Somos_, Dec 03 2016

A016137.name: Expansion of 1/((1-3x)(1-6x)).
formula: a(n) = (3^n)*Stirling2(n+2, 2), n >= 0, with Stirling2(n, m) = A008277(n, m).
With leading zero, this is (6^n - 3^n)/3, the binomial transform of A016127 (with extra leading zero). - _Paul Barry_, Aug 20 2003
With leading zero, this is the fourth binomial transform of A001045, with a(n) = (2^n-1)(3^n/3 - 0^n/3) = A000225(n)*(A000244(n-1) - 0^n/3). - _Paul Barry_, Apr 28 2004

A016138.name: Expansion of 1/((1-3x)(1-7x)).
formula: a(n) = ((5+sqrt4)^n - (5-sqrt4)^n)/4 in Fibonacci form. Offset 1. a(3)=79. - Al Hakanson (hawkuu(AT)gmail.com), Dec 31 2008

A016142.name: Expansion of 1/((1-3x)(1-9x)).
formula: a(n-1) = Sum_{i=1..n} binomial(n, i)*3^(n-i)*6^(i-1). - Sam Handler (sam_5_5_5_0(AT)yahoo.com), Jun 29 2004

A016149.name: Expansion of 1/((1-4*x)*(1-6*x)).
formula: a(n) = 10*a(n-1)-24*a(n-2) for n>1, a(0)=1. - _Barry E. Williams_, Jan 13 2000
a(n) = A081199(n+1). Binomial transform of A080961. - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 18 2008

A016150.name: Expansion of 1/((1-4x)(1-7x)).
formula: a(n) = 11*a(n-1)-28*a(n-2) for n>0, a(0)=1. - _Barry E. Williams_, Jan 13 2000

A016152.name: a(n) = 4^(n-1)*(2^n-1).
formula: a(n) = (4^(n-1))*stirling2(n+1, 2), n>=0, with stirling2(n, m)=A008277(n, m).
((6+sqrt4)^n - (6-sqrt4)^n)/4 in Fibonacci form. Offset 1. a(3)=112. - Al Hakanson (hawkuu(AT)gmail.com), Dec 31 2008

A016161.name: Expansion of 1/((1-5x)(1-7x)).
formula: a(n) = (7^(n+1)-5^(n+1))/2 = A081200(n+1). Binomial transform of A080962. - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 18 2008

A016163.name: Expansion of 1/((1-5x)(1-9x)).
formula: a(n) = ((7+sqrt4)^n - (7-sqrt4)^n)/4. Offset 1. a(3)=151. - Al Hakanson (hawkuu(AT)gmail.com), Dec 31 2008

A016164.name: Expansion of 1/((1-5x)(1-10x)).
formula: a(n) = (5^n)*Stirling2(n+2, 2), n >= 0, with Stirling2(n, m) = A008277(n, m).

A016169.name: a(n) = 7^n - 6^n.
formula: E.g.f.: e^(7*x) - e^(6*x). [_Mohammad K. Azarian_, Jan 14 2009]

A016170.name: Expansion of 1/((1-6x)(1-8x)).
formula: a(n) = 4*8^n-3*6^n = A081201(n+1). Binomial transform of A081033. [_R. J. Mathar_, Sep 18 2008]

A016175.name: Expansion of 1/((1-6x)(1-12x)).
formula: a(n) = (6^n)*Stirling2(n+2, 2), n >= 0, with Stirling2(n, m) = A008277(n, m).

A016177.name: a(n) = 8^n - 7^n.
formula: E.g.f.: e^(8*x) - e^(7*x). - _Mohammad K. Azarian_, Jan 14 2009

A016178.name: Expansion of 1/((1-7x)(1-9x)).
formula: a(n) = (9^(n+1) - 7^(n+1))/2 = A081202(n+1). Binomial transform of A081034. - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 18 2008

A016183.name: Expansion of 1/((1-7x)(1-11x)).
formula: ((9+sqrt4)^n - (9-sqrt4)^n)/4 in Fibonacci form. Offset 1. a(3)=247. - Al Hakanson (hawkuu(AT)gmail.com), Dec 31 2008

A016185.name: a(n) = 9^n - 8^n.
formula: E.g.f.: e^(9*x) - e^(8*x). - _Mohammad K. Azarian_, Jan 14 2009

A016186.name: Expansion of 1/((1-8x)(1-10x)).
formula: a(n) = 5*10^n - 4*8^n = A081203(n+1). Binomial transform of A081035. - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 18 2008

A016189.name: a(n) = 10^n - 9^n.
formula: E.g.f.: e^(10*x) - e^(9*x). - _Mohammad K. Azarian_, Jan 14 2009

A016195.name: a(n) = 11^n - 10^n.
formula: E.g.f.: e^(11*x) - e^(10*x). - _Mohammad K. Azarian_, Jan 14 2009

A016203.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)(1-2x)(1-8x)).
formula: a(n) = (4*8^(n+1) - 7*2^(n+1) + 3)/21. - _Mitch Harris_, Jun 27 2005 - corrected by _Yahia Kahloune_, May 06 2013

A016205.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)(1-2x)(1-10x)).
formula: a(n) = 10*a(n-1) + 2^(n+1) - 1 if n > 0; a(0)=1. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Feb 09 2011

A016209.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)(1-3x)(1-5x)).
formula: E.g.f.: (25*exp(5*x) - 18*exp(3*x) + exp(x))/8, from the e.g.f. of the third column (k=2) of A039755. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, May 26 2017

A016223.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)(1-4x)(1-7x)).
formula: E.g.f.: exp(x)*(1 - 32*exp(3*x) + 49*exp(6*x))/(2!*3^2). - This is (d^2/dx^2) (exp(x)*(exp(x) - 1)^2 / (2*3^2)). See also the second column of the Sheffer triangle A282629 divided by 3^2. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Apr 08 2017

A016232.name: Inverse of 2223rd cyclotomic polynomial.
formula: G.f.: 1/C_2223(x), where C_n(x) is the n-th cyclotomic polynomial.
a(n) = 0 if n is not divisible by 3.

A016238.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)*(1-5*x)*(1-11*x)).
formula: a(n) = 16*a(n-1) - 55*a(n-2) + 1 for n>1, a(0)=1, a(1)=17. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Feb 10 2011

A016243.name: Expansion of 1/((1-x)(1-6x)(1-8x)).
formula: a(n) = 14*a(n-1) - 48*a(n-2) + 1 with a(0)=1, a(1)=15. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Feb 10 2011

A016269.name: Number of monotone Boolean functions of n variables with 2 mincuts. Also number of Sperner systems with 2 blocks.
formula: If we define f(m,j,x) = Sum_{k=j..m} (binomial(m,k)*Stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k)) then a(n-2) = f(n,2,2), (n >= 2). - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009
E.g.f.: (d^2/dx^2) (exp(2*x)*((exp(x)-1)^2)/2!). See the Sheffer comment given above. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 08 2011

A016274.name: Numbers k where the fractional part of tan(k) decreases monotonically to 0.

A016283.name: a(n) = 6^n/8 - 4^(n-1) + 2^(n-3).
formula: a(n) = (2^n)*Stirling2(n+3, 3), n >= 0, with Stirling2(n, m) = A008277(n, m).

A016290.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-4x)(1-8x)).
formula: Difference of Gaussian binomial coefficients [ n+1, 3 ] - [ n, 3 ] (n >= 2).

A016304.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2*x)*(1-6*x)*(1-7*x)).
formula: a(n) = (7^(n+2) - 2^(n+2))/5-(6^(n+2) - 2^(n+2))/4. - _Zerinvary Lajos_, Jun 05 2009 [corrected by _Joerg Arndt_, Aug 25 2011]

A016309.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2*x)*(1-6*x)*(1-12*x)).
formula: a(n) = det(|ps(i+3,j+2)|, 1 <= i,j <= n), where ps(n,k) are Legendre-Stirling numbers of the first kind (A129467). - _Mircea Merca_, Apr 06 2013

A016321.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-9x)(1-10x)).
formula: From _Zerinvary Lajos_, Jun 05 2009 [corrected by _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 14 2011]: (Start)

A016325.name: Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1-10x)(1-11x)).
formula: From _Zerinvary Lajos_, Jun 05 2009 [corrected by _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 14 2011]: (Start)

A016430.name: Coordination sequence T1 for Zeolite Code OSI.

A016431.name: Coordination sequence T2 for Zeolite Code OSI.

A016432.name: Coordination sequence T3 for Zeolite Code OSI.

A016433.name: Coordination sequence T1 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016434.name: Coordination sequence T2 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016435.name: Coordination sequence T3 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016436.name: Coordination sequence T4 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016437.name: Coordination sequence T5 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016438.name: Coordination sequence T6 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016439.name: Coordination sequence T7 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016440.name: Coordination sequence T8 for Zeolite Code TER.

A016578.name: Decimal expansion of log(3/2).
formula: Equals Sum {k>=1} 1/(k*3^k). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Aug 08 2011

A016579.name: Decimal expansion of log(5/2).
formula: Equals A016628 minus A002162. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 23 2009

A016627.name: Decimal expansion of log(4).
formula: log(4) = Sum_{k >= 1} H(k)/2^k where H(k) is the k-th harmonic number. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Jun 15 2003
Equals 2*A002162 = Sum_{n >= 1} binomial(2*n, n)/(n*4^n) [D. H. Lehmer, Am. Math. Monthly 92 (1985) 449 and Jolley eq. 262]. - _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 04 2009
log(4) = Sum_{k >= 1} A191907(4, k)/k, (conjecture). - _Mats Granvik_, Jun 19 2011
log(4) = lim_{n -> infinity} A066066(n)/n. - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 20 2013
Equals Sum_{k >= 1} 1/( 2*k^2 - k ). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Aug 31 2014
Equals gamma(0, 1/2) - gamma(0, 1) = -(EulerGamma + polygamma(0, 1/2)), where gamma(n,x) denotes the generalized Stieltjes constants. - _Peter Luschny_, May 16 2018

A016631.name: Decimal expansion of log(8).
formula: Equals 2 + Sum_{n >= 1} 1/( n*(16*n^2 - 1) ). This summation was the first problem submitted by Ramanujan to the Journal of the Indian Mathematical Society. See Berndt, Corollary on p. 29. - _Peter Bala_, Feb 25 2015

A016639.name: Decimal expansion of log(16).
formula: Equals Sum_{k=1..4} (-1)^(k+1) gamma(0, k/4) where gamma(n,x) denotes the generalized Stieltjes constants. - _Peter Luschny_, May 16 2018
Equals -2 + Sum_{k>=1} H(k)*(k+1)/2^k, where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number. - _Amiram Eldar_, May 28 2021

A016648.name: Decimal expansion of log(25).
formula: Equals 10 * Sum_{k>=1} F(k)^2/(k * 4^k), where F(k) is the k-th Fibonacci number (A000045). - _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 09 2020

A016650.name: Decimal expansion of log(27).
formula: Log(27) = Integral_{x = 0..inf} sin(4*x)^3/x^2 dx. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 04 2019

A016655.name: Decimal expansion of log(32) = 5*log(2).
formula: Equals (5/4) Sum_{k=1..4} (-1)^(k+1) gamma(0, k/4) where gamma(n,x) denotes the generalized Stieltjes constants. - _Peter Luschny_, May 16 2018

A016725.name: Number of integer solutions to x^2+y^2+z^2 = n^2, allowing zeros and distinguishing signs and order.
formula: a(n) = 6 * b(n) if n>0 where b(n) is multiplicative with b(2^e) = 1, b(p^e) = p^e if p == 1 (mod 4), b(p^e) = p^e + 2 * (p^e - 1) / (p - 1) if p == 3 (mod 4). - _Michael Somos_, Nov 18 2011
a(n) = [x^(n^2)] theta_3(x)^3, where theta_3() is the Jacobi theta function. - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 20 2018

A016726.name: Smallest k such that 1, 4, 9, ..., n^2 are distinct mod k.
formula: For n > 4, a(n) is smallest k >= 2n such that k = p or k = 2p, p a prime.

A016727.name: Number of inequivalent solutions to x^2+y^2+z^2 = n^2.

A016728.name: Number of integer points (x,y,z) at distance <= 0.5 from sphere of radius n.

A016729.name: Highest minimal Hamming distance of any Type 4^H+ Hermitian additive self-dual code over GF(4) of length n.

A016741.name: Initial pile sizes which guarantee a win for player 2 in a certain variant of NIM.

A016742.name: Even squares: a(n) = (2*n)^2.
formula: a(n) = A155955(n,2) for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 31 2009
a(n) = A000384(n) + A014105(n). - _Bruce J. Nicholson_, Nov 11 2017

A016753.name: Expansion of 1/((1-3*x)*(1-4*x)*(1-5*x)).
formula: If we define f(m,j,x) = Sum_{k=j..m} binomial(m,k)*stirling2(k,j)*x^(m-k) then a(n-2) = f(n,2,3), (n >= 2). - _Milan Janjic_, Apr 26 2009

A016754.name: Odd squares: a(n) = (2n+1)^2. Also centered octagonal numbers.
formula: a(n) = 1 + Sum_{i=1..n} 8*i = 1 + 8*A000217(n). - Xavier Acloque, Jan 21 2003; _Zak Seidov_, May 07 2006; _Robert G. Wilson v_, Dec 29 2010
a(n) = a(n-1) + 8*n with n>0, a(0)=1. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 01 2010
Limit as n -> infinity of a(n)/a(n-1) = 1.
a(n) = A014105(n) + A000384(n+1). - _Bruce J. Nicholson_, Nov 11 2017

A016755.name: Odd cubes: a(n) = (2*n + 1)^3.
formula: E.g.f.: exp(x)*(1 + 26*x + 36*x^2 + 8*x^3). See A154537, row n=3. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Mar 12 2017

A016766.name: a(n) = (3*n)^2.
formula: a(n) = a(n-1) + 9*(2*n-1) for n>0, a(0)=0. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 19 2010

A016767.name: a(n) = (3*n)^3.
formula: a(n) = A155955(n,3) for n>2. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 31 2009
a(n) = -a(-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, Sep 16 2018

A016777.name: a(n) = 3*n + 1.
formula: a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - a(n-2); a(0)=1, a(1)=4. - _Philippe Deléham_, Nov 03 2008
E.g.f.: E(0), where E(k) = 1 + 3*x/(1 - 2*x/(2*x + 6*x*(k+1)/E(k+1) )); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jul 05 2013
G.f.: 1 + 4*x/(G(0) - 4*x), where G(k) = 1 + 4*x + 3*k*(x+1) -  x*(3*k+1)*(3*k+7)/G(k+1); (cont. fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jul 05 2013
a(n) = denominator(Sum_{k=0..n-1} 1/(a(k)*a(k+1)), with the numerator n = A001477(n), where the sum is set to 0 for n = 0. [Jolley, p. 38, (208)]
a(n) = -A016789(-1-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, May 27 2019

A016789.name: a(n) = 3*n + 2.
formula: a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - a(n-2); a(0)=2, a(1)=5. - _Philippe Deléham_, Nov 03 2008
a(n) = 6*n - a(n-1) + 1 with a(0)=2. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 25 2010
a(n) = n XOR A005351(n+1) XOR A005352(n+1) (conjectured). - _Gilian Breysens_, Jul 21 2017
a(n) = -A016777(-1-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, May 27 2019

A016803.name: (4n)^3.
formula: a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4) for n>3. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jul 05 2014

A016813.name: a(n) = 4*n + 1.
formula: G.f.: (1+3*x)/(1-x)^2. - _Paul Barry_, Feb 27 2003 [corrected for offset 0 by _Wolfdieter Lang_, Oct 03 2014]
a(n) = 8*n - 2 - a(n-1) for n > 0, a(0) = 1. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 20 2010
The identity (4*n+1)^2 - (4*n^2+2*n)*(2)^2 = 1 can be written as a(n)^2 - A002943(n)*2^2 = 1. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Mar 11 2009 - Nov 25 2012
Dirichlet g.f.: 4*Zeta(-1 + s) + Zeta(s). - _Stefano Spezia_, Nov 02 2018

A016814.name: a(n) = (4n+1)^2.
formula: a(n) = a(n-1) + 32 * n - 8, n > 0. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Dec 15 2010
a(0) = 1, a(n) = a(n - 1) + 32(n - 1) - 8. - _Alonso del Arte_, Aug 19 2017
Sum_{n>=0} 1/a(n) = G/2 + Pi^2/16, where G is the Catalan constant (A006752). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 28 2020

A016825.name: Positive integers congruent to 2 mod 4: a(n) = 4*n+2, for n >= 0.
formula: a(n) = A118413(n+1,2) for n>1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 27 2006
a(n) = 8*n - a(n-1) for n>0, a(0)=2. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 20 2010
From _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 11 2012, Jun 30 2012 and Jul 20 2012: (Start)
a(n) = T(n+2) - T(n-2) where T(n) = n*(n+1)/2 = A000217(n). In general, if M(k,n) = 2*k*n + k, then M(k,n) = T(n+k) - T(n-k). - _Charlie Marion_, Feb 24 2020

A016826.name: a(n) = (4n + 2)^2.
formula: Sum_{n>=0} (-1)^n/a(n) = G/4, where G is the Catalan constant (A006752). (End)

A016837.name: Primes reached after k iterations of sum of n and its prime divisors = t (where t replaces n in each iteration).
formula: Factor n, add n and its prime divisors. Sum = t, t replaces n, repeat until a prime is produced.

A016838.name: a(n) = (4n + 3)^2.
formula: Denominators of first differences Zeta[2,(4n-1)/4]-Zeta[2,(4(n+1)-1)/4]. - _Artur Jasinski_, Mar 03 2010
Sum_{n>=0} 1/a(n) = Pi^2/16 - G/2, where G is the Catalan constant (A006752). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 28 2020
Product_{n>=0} (1 - 1/a(n)) = Gamma(3/4)^2/sqrt(Pi) = A068465^2 * A087197. - _Amiram Eldar_, Feb 01 2021

A016861.name: a(n) = 5*n + 1.
formula: Row sums of triangle A131843. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Jul 21 2007
a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - a(n-2) with a(0)=1, a(1)=6. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 01 2010

A016897.name: a(n) = 5n + 4.
formula: A000041(a(n)) == 0 mod 5 is the first of Ramanujan's congruences. - _Ivan N. Ianakiev_, Dec 29 2014

A016910.name: a(n) = (6*n)^2.
formula: Product_{n>=1} a(n)/A136017(n) = Pi/3. - _Fred Daniel Kline_, Jun 09 2016
a(n) = t(9*n) - 9*t(n), where t(i) = i*(i+k)/2 for any k. Special case (k=1): a(n) = A000217(9*n) - 9*A000217(n). - _Bruno Berselli_, Aug 31 2017

A016911.name: a(n) = (6*n)^3.
formula: a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4) for n>3. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jul 05 2014

A016945.name: a(n) = 6*n+3.
formula: a(n) = 12*n - a(n-1) for n>0, a(0)=3. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Nov 20 2010

A016969.name: a(n) = 6*n + 5.
formula: a(n) = A007310(2*n+1); complement of A016921 with respect to A007310. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 02 2008
a(n) = floor((12n-1)/2) with offset 1..a(1)=5. - _Gary Detlefs_, Mar 07 2010

A016981.name: Expansion of 1/((1-3x)(1-4x)(1-10x)).
formula: a(n) = 14*a(n-1) -40*a(n-2) +3^n for n>1, a(0)=1, a(1)=17. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jun 26 2013

A016983.name: a(n) = (7*n)^3.
formula: a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4) for n > 3. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jul 05 2014
